    "summary": "Eric Melse area of interest is research into the effects of vocational skills in the connection between education and the labor market. He is interested in explorative analysis and visualization of data for personal development and professional training. For ten years he was senior lecturer at the Faculty of Business and Economics of the Hogeschool van Amsterdam.\n\nMelse has been working in the ICT industry since 1984. He has held positions as a consultant and ICT manager as well as managing director of several firms. He worked for KPMG Management Consultants, Oasis BV, Paradigm BV, Randstad (Yacht), the Ministry of Education (OCW) and the Careyn Group (CAG). Melse gained extensive experience with leading innovation teams both for software application development, for hardware deployment and networks (ICT infrastructures).\n\nMelse was appointed at Nyenrode Business Universiteit in 2007 at the Strategy Center. He also was director of the full time MSc degree program which was voted the best MSc in business management in the Netherlands in 2009 and again in 2010 (Keuzegids Masters 2011).\n\nHis research focuses on business intelligence and visual analytics, spectral map analysis (Spectramap), time series analysis (Eviews), dynamic modeling and simulation (Powersim, Vensim). Methods, tools and techniques for exploratory data analysis and visualization have his special interest (Stata, R, SPSS).\n\nMelse studied Information Analysis & Management at the Rijksuniversiteit Utrecht (post doc). At the Vrije Universiteit, Amsterdam, he studied art history, logic and epistemology. He completed his MBA at Bradford University/Nimbas in 1992. He received his PhD at Maastricht University with the thesis: Accounting for Trends. Relevance, explanatory and predictive power of force & momentum accounting. He published articles both in professional and academic journals.\n\nSpecialties: ICT management, management of change, business intelligence, strategy consulting, innovation, visual analytics, Spectramap, Foliomap, Stata, time series analysis, momentum accounting, dynamic simulation, color theory, color design & art",
